<br>
I have one or two people I really don't want to have much to do with.  I haven't even /ignored them, so far.  I have encountered one guild which seems to have a bizarre mix of folks - My encounters with folk from that guild have both high positive and high negative ratings, very dynamic.<br>
<br>
There is a tendancy to be wary after a bad experience with someone.  We all have it to one degree or another.   But if other folk in a guild, including the officers of course, at least *try* to deal with a specific case, then a good faith effort can go far to alleviating any long term considerations of dealing with that group of folk, even if an individual there becomes a no-no.<br>
<br>
But it's impossible to screen out all the loonies, no matter how hard you try.  And if you try too hard, you won't ever recruit to begin with.<br>
<br>
Morgen Ayanamii, speaking for herself<br>
Circle of Sisters <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uelsbetsquishytoes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>elsbet squishytoes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Grey</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 6:20:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild Name Damage Control</span><hr size=1> I travel this world with the name of my guild in tow.  Whereever I go, the name of &lt;Starspun&gt; follows.  This guild medallion, by decree, is fully visible at all times by anyone, and I be proud to wear it.  I am blessed with a good family, that sees things much the same way as I, and I am embarrassed of none of them.<br>
<br>
I do me best to be honest, honorable, and consistent in what I do in this world.  I strive to ensure that my family and guild name remain in good favor.  I can only be one person in this world, and I hope to be the best person that I can.<br>
