<br>
Some, like F&amp;F and Clan Were, have level restrictions on them and so limit their applicants, but most of the others that I am familiar with do not.  In the 20-30 level range, there are a fair number of unguilded folks out there.  <br>
<br>
My regular hunting partner and I have been looking for a guild to call home for a while, especially since finding groups is becoming less easy.  Surprisingly, this has not been a simple task – many of the guilds we are interested in (won’t mention names) are insular enough that it’s tough to get to know the members.<br>
