<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxsatyrx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xsatyrx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 12:59:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild Name Damage Control</span><hr size=1> Aye, in actuality, Society of Valor is having no problems find members. We are strong and prospering now....but getting the first 10 for formation was a Biotch! Now there is no problem at all....what provoked this thread...well i was slightly disturbed about a post one made after i was given Kudos by another. It is my opinion that even if one of us were given Kudos for something that we find no big deal, we pass it up. This person did not, but gave reason why Kudos werent necessary for my actions. I personally appreciated the fact the the Kudos Bearer would post his appreciation as he did because it was way out of my way. Did i expect Kudos?...No, but being i recieved them felt good and i enjoyed it. And the other poster lessened it by his post...so i thought id make a post here to explain that. My post main reason seems to be lost in the text...which is simply the guild leaders are not required to fix their guildmembers screwups. and if one goes out of his way to correct a wrong...it would be wise to give him respect. To those who feel no respect is needed...give me advance warning and i wont waste my time. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxsatyrx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xsatyrx</A> at: 1/9/02 1:11:19 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uhelmgest.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Helmgest</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 1:22:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild Name Damage Control</span><hr size=1> &gt;I see it like this, if you apply for a guild and they say 'your<br>
